The tallest man ever recorded in history is recognized by the Guinness World Records as Robert Wadlow of the United States [1][2]. When last measured on 27 June 1940 [3], he stood at 8 feet, 11.1 inches (2.72 meters) tall. Wadlow was born on February 22, 1918, and he died on July 15, 1940, at the age of 22 years due to complications from an infection. His remarkable height remains a subject of interest and fascination even today.